result.name: China Land Restaurant

reviews.text: This Shanghai restaurant is above average and I recommend you to have a try. I went there during weekend evening and need to wait for 40mins for a seat. Plan to get there earlier

I wanted to review this place because Ive eaten so much water boil beef in HK i must have eliminated an entire branch of the ancestral cattle family tree so I feel like i can spot some good water boil beef when i see some. Let me say that im ok with super spicy, but must have flavor to back up that spice. This place was not super spicy but still the flavor was quite good. Despite this it failed to hit the mark that some local wet market food shops are able to hit such as the one above the wet market in Sheung Shui. However for the price and amount of food that you get, it was a good deal in HK terms. The noodles hit the google review ranking in the junk however and were not all that good to be polite. The water boil beef however was worth a stop but if your in the market for some spicy boiled cattle perhaps hit the market in Sheung Shui instead, its just a mid walk away✌️
A bit salty but very good price for the food. Must try in fanling area.
Good service,  my favourite food

The foods are quite good, unfortunately, the services are quite lousy, two male waiters are no manner, treat us like dirt, I was asking for some tissues, one of the elder waiter gave us some dirty tissues, when I asked him to chance another tissues for us, he just walk away and pretend not hearing us, so I turn to another taller and younger waiter, he even worst, although he answered and gave us some new tissues, but we felt that his tones was unfriendly, didn't want to do it but due to fullfil the customer need, he Had to serve us...Both of them were not friendly and this kind of services we will give this restaurant a 3-4 points out of 10. I will give it a minus point if not because of the food...So please watch out for the waiter, one elderly another tall waiter if you going to the restaurant next time...

result.name: 湘川滬

reviews.text: 鍋貼底層脆卜卜裏面充滿肉質, 內裏有大粒蝦仁,對蝦敏感的朋友要注意. 片皮鴨亦不錯, 外皮鬆脆不油膩, 符合一般香港式片皮鴨, 比起正宗北京油脂較少, 但感覺上健康一點, 另外甜醬應是自家再處理, 混合了豆瓣醬, 甜中帶點野味, 層次比較豐富. 比較可惜的是包皮太厚, 未能做到透光, 以及沒有蠟燭蒸籠保持溫度. 另外可能是空間問題, 上菜時未能於你面前將片皮鴨切片. 當天價錢參考,片皮鴨$268, 四隻鍋貼$38, 茶位6$, 另收加一.
食品一般，每位茶錢照收，重要加一，加加下（貴過一個小菜）
今晚想食上海菜,出奇地唔使等位,先叫一客生煎包,要先叫因為煎包等好耐,小菜太多選擇..,二人只有叫一個酸菜魚🐟,菜飯.好味,但魚肉較多骨,要小心食.酸菜的營養價值好大,含維生素C，氨基酸，膳食纖維和其他營養成分。由於酸菜使用乳酸菌優勢菌的儲存方法，因此含有大量的乳酸菌。人體腸道中的正常菌群具有維持胃腸道正常生理功能的作用。😆👍
This Shanghai restaurant is above average and I recommend you to have a try. I went there during weekend evening and need to wait for 40mins for a seat. Plan to get there earlier
兩次都係食午餐，都係炸物多，但算不錯，40幾蚊，有飯有餸有小食。
